## Pydantic Validation Testing (CRITICAL for Python)
When testing Pydantic models (v2.x):
- Pydantic v2 error messages use format: "String should have at least X characters" (NOT v1 format "ensure this value has at least X characters")
- Custom validator errors with `raise ValueError("msg")` appear as: "Value error, msg" (Pydantic v2 adds "Value error, " prefix)
- Use case-insensitive substring matching: `assert "string should have" in str(exc.value).lower()` or `assert "value error" in str(exc.value).lower()`
- DO NOT use exact string matching like `assert exc.value == "exact message"` as Pydantic versions differ
- Test error type/category rather than exact message text where possible

Example test pattern:
```python
def test_validation_error():
    with pytest.raises(ValidationError) as exc_info:
        MyModel(field="invalid")
    # CORRECT: Case-insensitive substring matching
    assert "string should have" in str(exc_info.value).lower()
    # WRONG: Exact match fails across Pydantic versions
    # assert "String should have at least 1 character" == str(exc_info.value)
```
